<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-20T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-20T11:00:00-05:00" n="1143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1143">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/253</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Blocker</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Eagle Pass</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-20T10:00:00-06:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1916, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Governor State of Coahuila yesterday ordered all military commanders in
                            neighborhood of American ranches within a radius of <pb facs="0856" n="780" xml:id="pg_780"/> one hundred miles of the border to
                            immediately begin gathering of all horses and cattle thereon and to
                            collect them into moderate size herds, driving them southward toward
                            Saitillo. Approximately three million dollars worth American property is
                            involved. Vice Consul is informed soldiers have been dispatched to begin
                            rounding up to-day. American owners have been informed by military
                            authorities that order from governor is imperative. Suggest Department
                            act immediately before cattle are taken from their ranches.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blocker</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>